---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Asset Division in Maryland Divorce | Equitable Distribution Attorneys | Child Custody with a Plan"
  description="Maryland follows equitable distribution — not 50/50. Our divorce attorneys fight for a fair share of marital property including real estate, retirement accounts, and investments. Call (301) 289-8917."
  ogTitle="Maryland Asset Division Attorneys | Equitable Distribution | Child Custody with a Plan"
  ogDescription="Protect your financial future. Our Maryland divorce attorneys ensure equitable — not equal — division of marital assets. Rockville & Baltimore offices."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 bg-[url('/grid.svg')] bg-repeat"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-[#D4A843] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Maryland Marital Property Law</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-5">
        Asset Division in<br class="hidden md:block" /> Maryland Divorce
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Maryland is an equitable distribution state — "fair" doesn't mean "equal." We ensure the division of marital property truly reflects your contributions and circumstances.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[#0D6E6E] transition-colors">
          (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-3">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-[#0D6E6E]">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/divorce" class="hover:text-[#0D6E6E]">Divorce</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-800 font-medium">Asset Division</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Maryland Law Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-5">How Maryland Divides Marital Property</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Under Maryland Family Law § 8-205, courts have broad authority to distribute marital property based on what is "fair and just" — not necessarily equal. This means a judge analyzes a range of statutory factors before making a property award.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Maryland does <strong>not</strong> divide property in a single step. Instead, the court first determines what is marital versus non-marital, then values marital property, and finally makes a monetary award to balance any inequity in how titled assets are distributed.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            This three-step framework creates significant strategic opportunities — and risks. Having skilled legal counsel is critical to ensuring the court has all the facts needed to make a truly equitable determination.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Maryland's 3-Step Property Division Process</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3">
              {[
                { step: "1", text: "Classify — Identify what is marital property vs. non-marital (separate) property" },
                { step: "2", text: "Value — Determine the fair market value of all marital assets and debts" },
                { step: "3", text: "Distribute — Award property equitably using the § 8-205 factors" }
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
                  <span class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">{item.step}</span>
                  <span class="text-white/90 text-sm">{item.text}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-[#D4A843]/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong class="text-[#D4A843]">Important:</strong> Maryland courts cannot transfer title to property held in one spouse's name. Instead, the court uses "monetary awards" to balance the equities — making proper legal strategy essential.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Marital vs Non-Marital -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">Marital vs. Non-Marital Property</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Understanding the distinction between marital and separate property is the foundation of every asset division case.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-l-4 border-[#0D6E6E] shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#0D6E6E] mb-4">Marital Property (Subject to Division)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            {[
              "All property acquired during the marriage",
              "Income earned by either spouse during marriage",
              "Real estate purchased during marriage (even if titled in one name)",
              "Retirement contributions made during marriage",
              "Business interests developed or grown during marriage",
              "Joint bank accounts and investment accounts",
              "Vehicles purchased during marriage",
              "Appreciation on non-marital property due to marital effort"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#0D6E6E] font-bold">✓</span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-l-4 border-gray-400 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-700 mb-4">Non-Marital Property (Typically Excluded)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            {[
              "Property owned before the marriage",
              "Inheritances received by one spouse (even during marriage)",
              "Gifts given to one spouse from a third party",
              "Property excluded by a valid prenuptial agreement",
              "Proceeds from personal injury claims (pain and suffering)",
              "Property directly traceable to non-marital sources",
              "Property kept entirely separate and not commingled"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-gray-400 font-bold">✗</span>
                <span>{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-4 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-3">
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600"><strong>Note:</strong> Commingling non-marital assets with marital funds can convert them into marital property. Tracing is critical.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Statutory Factors -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">Factors Courts Consider Under MD § 8-205</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Maryland courts examine all relevant circumstances to determine what distribution is equitable. These factors guide our legal strategy.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {[
          { factor: "Length of Marriage", desc: "Longer marriages often result in more equal division" },
          { factor: "Monetary Contributions", desc: "Income, property, and financial investments by each spouse" },
          { factor: "Non-Monetary Contributions", desc: "Homemaking, childcare, and support of the other spouse's career" },
          { factor: "Circumstances That Contributed to Breakdown", desc: "Adultery, abuse, or other fault may be considered" },
          { factor: "Age and Health", desc: "Physical and mental health of both spouses" },
          { factor: "Economic Circumstances", desc: "Current income, earning potential, and financial needs" },
          { factor: "How Property Was Acquired", desc: "Source of funds, timing, and method of acquisition" },
          { factor: "Obligations and Rights", desc: "Existing debts, legal obligations, and claims against property" },
          { factor: "Any Other Relevant Factor", desc: "Courts have discretion to weigh any appropriate consideration" }
        ].map(f => (
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{f.factor}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{f.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Types of Assets -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#0D6E6E]">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white text-center mb-3">Asset Types We Handle</h2>
      <p class="text-white/75 text-center mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Our attorneys have experience valuing and dividing all types of marital assets — from straightforward bank accounts to complex financial instruments.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {[
          { icon: "🏠", title: "Marital Home & Real Estate", desc: "Primary residence, rental properties, vacation homes — we address valuation, buyout, and sale options." },
          { icon: "💰", title: "Retirement Accounts", desc: "401(k), 403(b), pensions, IRAs — we handle QDROs and ensure tax-efficient division." },
          { icon: "📈", title: "Investment Portfolios", desc: "Stocks, bonds, mutual funds, brokerage accounts — we account for unrealized gains and tax basis." },
          { icon: "🏢", title: "Business Interests", desc: "From LLCs to professional practices — we coordinate business valuation experts." },
          { icon: "🚗", title: "Vehicles & Personal Property", desc: "Cars, boats, jewelry, art, collectibles — properly valued and equitably distributed." },
          { icon: "💳", title: "Marital Debt", desc: "Mortgages, credit cards, loans — debt division is as important as asset division." }
        ].map(asset => (
          <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-xl p-5 text-white">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">{asset.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">{asset.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-white/80 text-sm">{asset.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Strategy -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-5">Our Asset Division Strategy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Asset division isn't just about what you get today — it's about what those assets mean for your financial security tomorrow. Our attorneys think long-term.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { title: "Comprehensive Asset Discovery", desc: "We identify all marital assets — including hidden, undervalued, or overlooked ones through discovery and subpoenas if necessary." },
              { title: "Expert Valuation Coordination", desc: "We work with certified business valuators, real estate appraisers, and forensic accountants to establish accurate values." },
              { title: "Tax-Conscious Division", desc: "We consider the after-tax value of every asset — not just the face value — to negotiate truly equitable outcomes." },
              { title: "Strategic Trade-Off Analysis", desc: "We help you understand the real-world implications of keeping the house versus a retirement account versus liquid assets." }
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex gap-4 items-start">
                <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-[#D4A843] rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm flex-shrink-0 mt-1">✓</span>
                <div>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900">{item.title}</strong>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">{item.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#0D6E6E] mb-4">Related Practice Areas</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            {[
              { title: "High-Net-Worth Divorce", link: "/high-net-worth-divorce" },
              { title: "Divorces Involving Businesses", link: "/divorces-involving-businesses" },
              { title: "Divorce for Professionals", link: "/divorce-lawyer-for-professionals" },
              { title: "Spousal Support / Alimony", link: "/spousal-support" },
              { title: "Divorce Overview", link: "/divorce" }
            ].map(area => (
              <a href={area.link} class="flex items-center justify-between p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#0D6E6E]/5 transition-colors group">
                <span class="text-gray-700 group-hover:text-[#0D6E6E] font-medium">{area.title}</span>
                <span class="text-[#D4A843]">→</span>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Protect Your Financial Future</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Don't leave the division of your marital assets to chance. Our Maryland divorce attorneys will fight to ensure you receive a fair and equitable outcome.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#0a5a5a] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Call (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">Rockville: 100 Park Ave Suite 205, MD 20850 · Baltimore: 1537 Light St #100, MD 21230</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
